FROM GITHUB.COM, HOW TO GIT :
    Global setup:

     Set up git
      git config --global user.name "goFrendiAsgard"
      git config --global user.email goFrendiAsgard@gmail.com
            

    Next steps:

      mkdir Chimera
      cd Chimera
      git init
      touch README
      git add README
      git commit -m 'first commit'
      git remote add origin git@github.com:goFrendiAsgard/Chimera.git
      git push -u origin master
          

    Existing Git Repo?

      cd existing_git_repo
      git remote add origin git@github.com:goFrendiAsgard/Chimera.git
      git push -u origin master
      
      
    After changing something
      
      git add . -A
      git commit -m 'the comment'
      git tag -a v1.4 -m 'version 1.4'
      git push -u origin master --tags   
